title: Spin resolved ECT-HOPE science data. Electron fluxes ~15-50,000 eV, ion fluxes ~1-50,000 eV. Electrons and ions measured in alternate spin cadence.  - Herbert Funsten (Los Alamos National Laboratory)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch_Ele' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/rbsp/rbspb/l2/ect/hope/sectors/rel04/2012/rbspb_rel04_ect-hope-sci-l2_20121025_v6.1.0.cdf. The most common cadence occurred for 43.7860% of the 1596 timesteps. Cadence = 24347 [ms] = PT24.347S.
info.contact: Herbert Funsten @ Los Alamos National Laboratory

parameters.name: Position_Ele_TT
parameters.description: [Labels on plots] Position of the satellite in geographic coordinates (ele). This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['Position_Ele']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
